      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: attribute spawned task runs to child agent",
        "body": "Fixes #66670\n\n## Summary\n- Attribute spawned subagent task records to the child/executing agent instead of the parent requester.\n- Pass the resolved `targetAgentId` through `sessions_spawn` registration and let task creation fall back to `childSessionKey` agent inference when an explicit agent id is missing.\n- Make gateway `tasks.list` treat an explicit `task.agentId` as authoritative, using the session-key fallback only for older records without an `agentId`, so a worker task owned by main is not listed under `agentId: main`.\n- Add regression coverage for task registry filtering, direct SQLite `task_runs.agent_id` persistence, the `sessions_spawn` registration seam, and gateway `tasks.list` agent attribution.\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: `sessions_spawn`/subagent task rows now persist `task_runs.agent_id` as the executing child agent for keys like `agent:worker:subagent:*`, while preserving parent owner/requester fields.\n\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout on Linux with a fresh `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`, using the repository runtime code and Node's SQLite driver to read the created `state/openclaw.sqlite` file.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: ran this command from the patched checkout:\n\n```bash\nnode --import tsx --input-type=module <<'NODE'\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport os from \"node:os\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport { DatabaseSync } from \"node:sqlite\";\nimport { createRunningTaskRun } from \"./src/tasks/task-executor.ts\";\nimport { resetTaskRegistryForTests } from \"./src/tasks/task-registry.ts\";\nimport { closeOpenClawStateDatabase } from \"./src/state/openclaw-state-db.ts\";\nimport { resolveOpenClawStateSqlitePath } from \"./src/state/openclaw-state-db.paths.ts\";\n\nconst stateDir = fs.mkdtempSync(path.join(os.tmpdir(), \"oc-agent-proof-\"));\nprocess.env.OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR = stateDir;\nresetTaskRegistryForTests({ persist: false });\n\nconst task = createRunningTaskRun({\n  runtime: \"subagent\",\n  ownerKey: \"agent:main:main\",\n  scopeKind: \"session\",\n  childSessionKey: \"agent:worker:subagent:proof\",\n  runId: \"run-proof-agent-id\",\n  task: \"Attribute spawned worker task\",\n  deliveryStatus: \"pending\",\n});\n\nconst sqlitePath = resolveOpenClawStateSqlitePath(process.env);\ncloseOpenClawStateDatabase();\nconst db = new DatabaseSync(sqlitePath, { readOnly: true });\nconst sqliteRow = db\n  .prepare(\"SELECT agent_id, owner_key, child_session_key, run_id, status FROM task_runs WHERE task_id = ?\")\n  .get(task.taskId);\ndb.close();\n\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify({ taskAgentId: task.agentId, sqliteRow, sqliteFile: path.relative(stateDir, sqlitePath) }, null, 2));\nNODE\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: terminal output from that command:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"taskAgentId\": \"worker\",\n  \"sqliteRow\": {\n    \"agent_id\": \"worker\",\n    \"owner_key\": \"agent:main:main\",\n    \"child_session_key\": \"agent:worker:subagent:proof\",\n    \"run_id\": \"run-proof-agent-id\",\n    \"status\": \"running\"\n  },\n  \"sqliteFile\": \"state/openclaw.sqlite\"\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: the copied live output shows the task registry record and the durable SQLite row both attribute the run to `worker`, while the parent owner remains `agent:main:main` and the child session key remains `agent:worker:subagent:proof`.\n\nWhat was not tested: a full interactive `sessions_spawn` turn against an existing user `~/.openclaw` directory; the command above exercises the same task creation and SQLite persistence path with an isolated OpenClaw state directory.\n\n## Follow-up: code-review findings\n\nTwo review findings addressed:\n\n1. **Test helper signature (`task-registry.test.ts`)** — the cross-agent attribution test passed `async (root)` to `withTaskRegistryTempDir`, whose signature is `run: () => Promise<T>` (it already sets `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR` internally). Removed the unused parameter and the redundant env assignment so `tsgo:core:test` / `check-test-types` pass (this was the only blocking CI failure).\n\n2. **Gateway `tasks.list` agent filtering (`src/gateway/server-methods/tasks.ts`)** — `taskMatchesAgent` fell through to a requester/owner/child session-key scan even when the task already had an explicit `agentId`. A worker subagent task owned by `agent:main:main` therefore also matched `agentId: main`. Now an explicit `task.agentId` is authoritative; the session-key fallback only applies to legacy records without an `agentId`.\n\nGateway regression (real `tasks.list` handler + real task registry):\n```\n# WITH FIX:\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/tasks.test.ts\nTests  10 passed (10)   # across 2 gateway shards\n# new test \"treats explicit task agentId as authoritative over the session-key fallback\":\n#   tasks.list { agentId: \"main\" }   -> []            (worker task not leaked)\n#   tasks.list { agentId: \"worker\" } -> [worker task]\n\n# NEGATIVE CONTROL (git-stash the gateway tasks.ts fix):\n# the new test fails: main's view leaks run-worker-authoritative via the session-key fallback\n```\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tasks/task-registry.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/tasks.test.ts` → task-registry 76 passed, gateway tasks 10 passed\n- negative control: revert the gateway `taskMatchesAgent` fix → the new gateway test fails (proves the fix is required); restoring the test-helper `root` param makes `tsgo:core:test` report the original TS2345/TS7006 at `task-registry.test.ts`\n- `tsgo:core` / `tsgo:core:test` → no new errors in changed files; `oxfmt` → clean\n",
